# UI Styling Consistency

When adding or modifying UI in the SolClaim app, follow these typography patterns for consistency.

## Tab Page Headers

- **Title**: `text-base font-black text-foreground uppercase tracking-widest`
- **Subtitle**: `text-[10px] text-muted-foreground mt-0.5 uppercase tracking-wider font-medium`

Example: Wallets ("Saved Wallets"), Settings ("SETTINGS")

## Card Section Headers

- **Standard**: `font-black text-sm text-foreground uppercase tracking-widest`
- **Small** (e.g. Leaderboard): `text-xs font-black text-foreground uppercase tracking-widest`

Example: "Receiver Wallet", "Batch Claim", "Leaderboard"

## Modal Titles

- **Modal title**: `text-xl font-black text-foreground uppercase tracking-widest`

Example: Set Receiver, Add Wallet, Enter Your Private Key

## Labels (form fields)

- **Label**: `text-[11px] font-black text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-widest`

## Stat Labels (small labels above values)

- **Primary**: `text-[10px] font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-widest`
- **Secondary**: `text-[10px] font-bold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-widest`

## Buttons

- **Primary CTAs**: `font-black` with rounded corners
- **Copy/outline buttons**: `font-bold uppercase tracking-wider` for action text

## Copy Buttons

Use "Copy" for copy-to-clipboard buttons (not "Copy current").
